{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"64224443-b36d-437d-9418-359c716259b2","content":"Here are the **evaluation performance issues** in this project:\n\n---\n\n### 1. File I/O Property Function (High Impact)\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nReading files via property functions runs during **evaluation** (before build starts) and blocks the MSBuild evaluation pass. This is synchronous I/O on every evaluation — including IDE design-time builds.\n\n**Fix:** Read the file in a target at execution time using `ReadLinesFromFile`, or use a custom task.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Expensive Glob Pattern (Medium Impact)\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\nA recursive `**\\*.*` glob walks the entire directory tree during evaluation. If the project sits in a directory with `node_modules`, `.git`, or other large subtrees, this becomes very expensive.\n\n**Fix:** Narrow the glob (`**\\*.txt`) or add large directories to `$(DefaultItemExcludes)`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Deep Import Chain (Low-Medium Impact)\n```\nEvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nThree levels of chained imports. With only 3 levels this is minor, but it's a pattern that scales poorly. Each import adds an evaluation pass. Flattening or consolidating shared settings reduces overhead.\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n| Issue | Severity | Recommendation |\n|-------|----------|----------------|\n| `File::ReadAllText` in property | High | Move to execution-time target |\n| `**\\*.*` glob | Medium | Narrow scope or exclude large dirs |\n| Chained imports | Low | Flatten if chain grows deeper |\n\nThe file I/O property function is the most impactful issue — it forces disk reads on every single evaluation, including background IDE evaluations.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"43dec013-3aa6-4f8a-ae0a-2192b360573c","outputTokens":459,"requestId":"2841:1CADF2:1C9295E:1FD21C3:69FA958F"},"id":"51e09008-0381-4597-be6f-5a7670be50e1","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:12:59.561Z","parentId":"2a7b45b4-7edc-4de4-9613-bd43794c6937"}
